<br>
On the other hand, I often use a low lv spell like shock of blades or bolt of flame to pull with, but at lv 8 (shock of blades) I couldn't hit a mob in SD for any damage. I do hit for damage with the spell, not a lot, but some. So your fiery friend will never nuke as good as a lv 45 wizard, but his nukes should land for some damage.<br>
<br>
Having said that, I will aggree that the fire pet IS a wuss compared to the other pets. Just doing a simple test, sending it is to kill a green mob you can time they use to kill stuff are 20-30% longer <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bottom line, I hope the lv 60+ fire pet is better, especially at nuking, but you will never-ever see it toss high lv wizard nukes or if it will toss high lv wizard nukes, it will do so very rarely and mele for 10 dmg.<br>
<br>
